ational metaphors, epileptic texts, and metastability to categorize and examine these foci further. Applying philosophy as well as "hard sciences" (i.e. mathematics, medicine, physics) to disability studies, her study of selected works by Siri Hustvedt, Thom Jones, Reif Larsen, Dennis Mahagin, Audrey Niffenegger, Rodman Philbrick, and Lauren Slater shows how epilepsy metaphors redefine the notion of the "liminal" and the "normal".  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aAmerican literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aAmerican literaturey21st centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEpilepsy in literature. 0aIndividuation (Psychology) in literature. 4aAmerican Studies. 4aBody. 4aConceptual Metaphors. 4aDisability Studies. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aLiterature. 4aMedicine. 4aMetastability. 4aNormativity. 4aSiri Hustvedt. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh  aAmerican Studies.  aBody.  aConceptual Metaphors.  aDisability Studies.  aLiterary Studies.  aLiterature.  aMedicine.  aMetastability.  aNormativity.  aSiri Hustvedt.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2017z9783110548198oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Contemporary eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311066154540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839441183zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839441183423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839441183/original